postcontent: Beautiful Mosin Nagant CarbineThe pictures do this no justice. This will be the last time I list this for sale. It's a Mosin Carbine I bought a few years back and one of the few Mosins I have kept in my collection. I only keep guns that I find are prestine enough that I may not find another in its condition which I believe this to be one of them. ( The ONLY thing wrong with this rifle ( that I have seen ) is the trigger pull. The trigger pull has a couple seconds of delaying the firing pin when pulled, but you can buy a brand new match grade trigger ( such as Timney ) that literally drop in for around $50. Which is what I had planned for the rifle, but I'm getting into newer guns and need to let a few old ones go even though the prices of these have doubled in the past years and will probably continue rising.) The gun also comes with an unserialized Bent Bolt ( these sell for $60+ easy alone in the condition this one is in. Looks professionally done or like an actual bent bolt pulled from a Mosin Sniper. I wouldn't sell it though as it makes for a much smoother operating action when used. That will be the buyers decision though. A regular beat up Mosin Carbine sells for $300-$350 easy these days so I'm asking $440 FIRM as people are starting to recognize the potential of this cartridge and rifle. I've been seeing modern guns are even starting to be produced in 7.62x54R now such as brand new AK Sniper Kolishinkov is still producing. This is one of the best rounds you will ever find and especially for the prices you can find them at in the surplus market.  I love the history behind the Mosin, the caliber , and the carbine models which are super hard to find these days from what I've seen so I won't be lowering the price. Sorry, so please no offers besides the listed price. I will sell the rifle and bolt separate if you do not want the bent bolt.
